Sappho
was
born
on

the
island
of
Lesbos
about
600
B.
C.
At
some
period
of
her
life

she
was
exiled
from
Lesbos.
The
tragedy
and
beauty
of
her

life
reveals
itself
to
us
in
her
poems.
She
is
a
woman
of

ardent
nature,
noble,
delicate-minded
and
fond
of
pleasure.
Her

poems
were
chiefly
love
poems

that
they
were
written
chiefly

to
women
is
clear,
even
from
the
mutilated
fragments
which
remain.
